<subSubSection id="2DF0ACA1FFFBFFC4FF71FB1DFDABFAFB" pageId="19" pageNumber="20" type="description">
<paragraph id="6555FF2AFFFBFFC4FF71FB1DFDD7FB47" blockId="19.[151,1436,1194,1365]" box="[151,554,1231,1257]" pageId="19" pageNumber="20">
(
<figureCitation id="FDD1E3AFFFFBFFC4FF79FB1DFF05FB47" box="[159,248,1231,1257]" captionStart="FIGURE 13" captionStartId="66.[151,250,1976,2000]" captionTargetBox="[210,1376,198,1943]" captionTargetId="figure-32@66.[201,1387,181,1952]" captionTargetPageId="66" captionText="FIGURE 13. Southeast Asian Eudocima and Eudocima sikhimensis group adults (dorsal aspect)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6605531" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6605531/files/figure.png" pageId="19" pageNumber="20">Figs 13</figureCitation>
: I–J, 21: A, 26: I–K, 32:D)
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="6555FF2AFFFBFFC4FF71FB21FDABFAFB" blockId="19.[151,1436,1194,1365]" pageId="19" pageNumber="20">
This species looks very similar to 
<taxonomicName id="A2EA84A9FFFBFFC4FDFEFB21FD45FAA3" baseAuthorityName="Butler" baseAuthorityYear="1895" box="[536,696,1267,1293]" class="Insecta" family="Noctuidae" genus="Eudocima" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="19" pageNumber="20" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="sikhimensis">
<emphasis id="579E2338FFFBFFC4FDFEFB21FD45FAA3" box="[536,696,1267,1293]" italics="true" pageId="19" pageNumber="20">E. sikhimensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
but it has broader wings and differs further as described above. It is found in the northeastern 
<collectingCountry id="1DFDBFBAFFFBFFC4FE35FAC5FDACFA9F" box="[467,593,1303,1329]" name="Philippines" pageId="19" pageNumber="20">Philippines</collectingCountry>
in Luzon and on the island of Mindoro (
<bibRefCitation id="017B82DBFFFBFFC4FBFAFAC5FAE5FA9F" author="Zilli, A. &amp; Hogenes, W." box="[1052,1304,1303,1329]" pageId="19" pageNumber="20" pagination="153 - 207" refId="ref41799" refString="Zilli, A. &amp; Hogenes, W. (2002) An annotated list of the fruit-piercing moth genus Eudocima Billberg, 1820 (sensu Poole) with descriptions of four new species (Lepidoptera: Noctuidae, Catocalinae). Quadrifina, 5, 153 - 207." type="journal article" year="2002">Zilli &amp; Hogenes 2002</bibRefCitation>
), especially around the higher elevations of Banaue.
</paragraph>
